{"id":31959,"date":"2022-03-03T13:58:30","date_gmt":"2022-03-03T21:58:30","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/?p=31959"},"modified":"2022-04-18T18:49:27","modified_gmt":"2022-04-19T01:49:27","slug":"hardware-3","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/coertvonk.com\/sw\/embedded\/opnpool-design\/hardware-3-31959","title":{"rendered":"Hardware"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>\r\n    The design of OPNpool hardware is based around a RS-485 Transceiver and an ESP32 System on a Chip (SoC). The transceiver converts between the RS-485 differential signals and the transmit\/receive signals used by the UART in the SoC. The ESP32 is supported by the well documented Espressif IoT Development Framework (ESP-IDF).\r\n<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\n    Early prototypes\r\n<\/h2>\r\n<p>\r\n    We started by using a single threaded task on a Espressif ESP8266 SoC. This was cheap and offered built-in WiFi, but over time, we migrated to the newer ESP32. Though still very affordable, and it also offers Bluetooth LE and runs FreeRTOS which helps in separating the software components.\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container tight\">\r\n        <figure>\r\n            <a href=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto1-copy.jpg\"><img  title=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto1-copy-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-32247\" srcset=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto1-copy-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto1-copy-400x300.jpg 400w, https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto1-copy-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto1-copy.jpg 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 89vw, (max-width: 767px) 82vw, 740px\" \/><\/a>\r\n            <figcaption>\r\n                1st prototype based on ESP8266,<br \/>with two RS-232-s and a RS485 transceiver.\r\n            <\/figcaption>\r\n        <\/figure>\r\n        <figure>\r\n            <a href=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto2-copy.jpg\"><img src=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto2-copy.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-32248\" srcset=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto2-copy.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto2-copy-400x300.jpg 400w, https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto2-copy-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 89vw, (max-width: 767px) 82vw, 740px\" \/><\/a>\r\n            <figcaption>\r\n                2nd prototype based on ESP8266,<br \/>with RS-232 and RS-485 transceivers.\r\n            <\/figcaption>\r\n        <\/figure>\r\n        <figure>\r\n            <a href=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto3-copy.jpg\"><img src=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto3-copy-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-32249\" srcset=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto3-copy-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto3-copy-400x300.jpg 400w, https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto3-copy-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto3-copy.jpg 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 89vw, (max-width: 767px) 82vw, 740px\" \/><\/a>\r\n            <figcaption>\r\n                3rd prototype based on ESP32<br \/>with RS-485 transceiver.\r\n            <\/figcaption>\r\n        <\/figure>\r\n        <figure>\r\n            <a href=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto4-copy.jpg\"><img src=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto4-copy-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-32250\" srcset=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto4-copy-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto4-copy-400x300.jpg 400w, https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto4-copy-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-hardware-proto4-copy.jpg 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 89vw, (max-width: 767px) 82vw, 740px\" \/><\/a>\r\n            <figcaption>\r\n                4th prototype based on a ESP32 development board<br\/>with a RS-485 transceiver.\r\n            <\/figcaption>\r\n        <\/figure>\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\n    ESP32 SoC\r\n<\/h2>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n    The official name of the ESP32 SoC is &#8220;ESP32-D0WDQ6&#8221;. It contains two CPUs and peripherals such as WiFi, Bluetooth and Bluetooth LE.\r\n<\/p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The <a href=\"https:\/\/www.espressif.com\/sites\/default\/files\/documentation\/esp32-wroom-32_datasheet_en.pdf\">ESP32-WROOM32<\/a> module combines this ESP32 with a clock circuit, 4 MByte flash memory and a trace antenna.\r\n    This in turn is mounted on a Wemos LOLIN D32 daughterboard, that provides the reset logic, USB bridge and battery circuit. The main reason for using the LOLIN D32, is that we didn&#8217;t want to solder the micro-USB connector ourselves. Looking back, it seems more cost effective as well.\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container tight\">\r\n        <figure>\r\n            <a href=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/lolin-d32-schematic-copy.svg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/lolin-d32-schematic-copy.svg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"525\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-32272\" \/><\/a>\r\n            <figcaption>\r\n                Schematic LOLIN-D32 daughterboard\r\n            <\/figcaption>\r\n        <\/figure>\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\n    Schematic\r\n<\/h2>\r\n<p>    \r\n    The schematic itself is pretty straightforward.  We take the power from the pool controller and convert it to 3.3 V, and a buck converter provides 5 Volts to the battery connector on the ESP32 daughterboard. Using the battery input helps prevent problems when the circuit is also powered through the USB connector\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container tight\">\r\n        <figure>\r\n            <a href=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-r2-schematic-power.svg\"><img src=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-r2-schematic-power.svg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-32253\" \/><\/a>\r\n            <figcaption>\r\n                Schematic OPNpool power\r\n            <\/figcaption>\r\n        <\/figure>\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The data path is between the RS-485 connector and the ESP32 on the LOLIN D32 daughterboard.  There is an optional terminator resistor to prevent reflections on the bus. The JTAG header is for debugging as detailed in the Debugging chapter.\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container tight\">\r\n        <figure>\r\n            <a href=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-r2-schematic-logic.svg\"><img src=\"https:\/\/coertvonk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/opnpool-r2-schematic-logic.svg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-32252\" \/><\/a>\r\n            <figcaption>\r\n                Schematic OPNpool logic\r\n            <\/figcaption>\r\n        <\/figure>\r\n    <\/div>\r\n<\/p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The second revision adds LEDs for RS-485 <code>RX<\/code> (green) and <code>TX<\/code> (amber) to simplify setup. It also introduces a push button to preform a factory reset, and increases the bore hole size for the screws.\r\n<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h3>\r\n    Bill of Materials\r\n<\/h3>\r\n<p>\r\n    The price comes down to under $40 based on single quantity, excluding shipping and taxes. However, note that some items, such as the PCB, have minimum order quantities.\r\n<\/p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <div class=\"flex-container\">\r\n        <table class=\"bom\">\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th width=\"15%\">Name<\/th>\r\n                <th>Description<\/th>\r\n                <th>Suggested mfr and part#<\/th>\r\n                <th>Paid<\/th>\r\n            <\/tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>PBC r2<\/td>\r\n                <td>Printed circuit board<\/td>\r\n                <td>OSHPark nS1z3Duu<\/td>\r\n                <td><a href=\"https:\/\/oshpark.com\/shared_projects\/nS1z3Duu\">$9.43<\/td>\r\n            <\/tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>ENCLOSURE<\/td>\r\n                <td>158x90x60mm clear plastic project enclosure, IP65<\/td>\r\n                <td><i>white label<\/i><\/td>\r\n                <td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.aliexpress.com\/item\/32807853175.html\">$8.65<\/a><\/td>\r\n            <\/tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>LOLIN D32<\/td>\r\n                <td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.wemos.cc\/en\/latest\/d32\/d32.html\">Wemos LOLIN D32, based on ESP-WROOM-32 4MB<\/a><\/td>\r\n                <td>Wemos LOLIN-D32<\/td>\r\n                <td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.aliexpress.com\/item\/32808551116.html\">$6.50<\/a><\/td>\r\n            <\/tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>RS485_CONN<\/td>\r\n                <td>Plug+socket, male+female, 5-pin, 16mm aviation, IP68<\/td>\r\n                <td>SD 16-5S<\/td>\r\n                <td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.aliexpress.com\/item\/32401149735.html\">$3.50<\/td>\r\n            <\/tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>MAX3485<\/td>\r\n                <td>Maxim MAX3485CSA, RS-485\/UART interface IC 3.3V, 8-SO<\/td>\r\n                <td>Analog-Devices MAX3490ECSA<\/td>\r\n                <td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.digikey.com\/en\/products\/detail\/analog-devices-inc-maxim-integrated\/MAX3485CSA-T\/1703654\">